iniCLIHookInstallation`  \\n- Subtest: \\\"installs all required hooks\\\" — InstallHooks(false, false) returns 7, AreHooksInstalled() true, settings.json contains all hook types\\n- Subtest: \\\"idempotent - second install returns 0\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"localDev mode uses go run\\\" — settings.json contains \\\"go run\\\" and \\\"${FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR}\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"production mode uses entire binary\\\" — settings.json contains \\\"entire hooks factoryai-droid\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"force flag reinstalls hooks\\\" — force=true returns 7 after initial install\\n- Subtest: \\\"adds permissions.deny rule\\\" — settings.json has `Read(./.entire/metadata/**)`\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidHelperMethods** — Mirror of `TestGeminiCLIHelperMethods`\\n- Subtest: \\\"FormatResumeCommand returns droid --session-id\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"GetHookConfigPath returns .factory/settings.json\\\"\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidSessionStubs** — Unique to Factory AI Droid (since ReadSession/WriteSession are stubs)\\n- Subtest: \\\"ReadSession returns not-implemented error\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"WriteSession returns not-implemented error\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"GetSessionDir returns not-implemented error\\\"\\n\\n### 2. Create `setup_factoryai_hooks_test.go` (mirror of `setup_gemini_hooks_test.go`):\\n\\n**TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_AddsAllRequiredHooks** — Smoke test for `entire enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Creates env, InitRepo, InitEntire, creates initial commit\\n- Runs `enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Verifies `.factory/settings.json` contains all 7 hook types\\n- Verifies permissions.deny rule\\n\\n**TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_PreservesExistingSettings** — Preserves custom settings\\n- Pre-populates `.factory/settings.json` with custom fields and user hooks\\n- Runs enable\\n- Verifies custom fields and user hooks preserved, our hooks added\\n\\n### 3. Add `FactoryDroidHookRunner` to `hooks.go`:\\n\\nA hook runner that simulates Factory AI Droid hooks, similar to `GeminiHookRunner`:\\n- `NewFactoryDroidHookRunner(repoDir string, t TestT) *FactoryDroidHookRunner`\\n- `SimulateUserPromptSubmit(sessionID string) error` — runs `entire hooks factoryai-droid user-prompt-submit`\\n- `SimulateStop(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error` — runs `entire hooks factoryai-droid stop`\\n- `SimulateSessionEnd(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error`\\n- `SimulatePreTask(sessionID, transcriptPath, toolUseID string) error`\\n- `SimulatePostTask(input PostTaskInput) error`\\n- Convenience methods on TestEnv: `SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmit`, `SimulateFactoryDroidStop`, etc.\\n\\nAlso add `FactoryDroidSession` struct and `NewFactoryDroidSession()` on TestEnv that creates sessions with JSONL transcripts.\\n\\n### 4. Add Factory AI Droid to `agent_strategy_test.go`:\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidAgentStrategyComposition** — Same as `TestAgentStrategyComposition` but using factoryai-droid agent. Since ReadSession returns \\\"not implemented\\\", this test should verify checkpoints work through the hook-based flow (UserPromptSubmit → Stop).\\n\\nNote: Since ReadSession is a stub, the strategy tests that depend on ReadSession (like transcript restoration) should be skipped or tested differently for Factory AI Droid.\\n\\n## Important considerations:\\n- Factory AI Droid uses the same JSONL transcript format as Claude Code, so the existing `TranscriptBuilder` and `NewSession` should work for creating test transcripts\\n- Tests that use `os.Chdir` cannot be parallel\\n- All other tests should use `t.Parallel()`\\n- Hook simulation runs the CLI binary via `exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"hooks\\\", \\\"factoryai-droid\\\", hookName)`\\n- The Factory AI Droid hooks don't need a project dir env var like Claude/Gemini (no `ENTIRE_TEST_FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR` needed since the agent doesn't use one for session resolution)\",\"agentId\":\"a9868ef\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_012zqVgRP1cccpT7yr9kEc2x\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016NtmS9a4tieVSYn3iCqNek\",\"uuid\":\"fc37efad-23db-4898-92a4-f702ec4c84e2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T21:45:27.913Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"fc37efad-23db-4898-92a4-f702ec4c84e2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d4e06782-5186-4133-bb90-098cac18412b\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"quiet-forging-kettle\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CLhZfFSJxgsUTbgNkNKnx6\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→//go:build integration\\n     2→\\n     3→package integration\\n     4→\\n     5→import (\\n     6→\\t\\\"crypto/sha256\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"encoding/hex\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n    10→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n    11→\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n    12→\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n    13→\\t\\\"runtime\\\"\\n    14→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    15→\\t\\\"testing\\\"\\n    16→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    17→\\n    18→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n    19→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint\\\"\\n    20→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id\\\"\\n    21→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil\\\"\\n    22→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths\\\"\\n    23→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy\\\"\\n    24→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers\\\"\\n    25→\\n    26→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5\\\"\\n    27→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing\\\"\\n    28→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/format/config\\\"\\n    29→\\t\\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/object\\\"\\n    30→)\\n    31→\\n    32→// testBinaryPath holds the path to the CLI binary built once in TestMain.\\n    33→// All tests share this binary to avoid repeated builds.\\n    34→var testBinaryPath string\\n    35→\\n    36→// getTestBinary returns the path to the shared test binary.\\n    37→// It panics if TestMain hasn't run (testBinaryPath is empty).\\n    38→func getTestBinary() string {\\n    39→\\tif testBinaryPath == \\\"\\\" {\\n    40→\\t\\tpanic(\\\"testBinaryPath not set - TestMain must run before tests\\\")\\n    41→\\t}\\n    42→\\treturn testBinaryPath\\n    43→}\\n    44→\\n    45→// TestEnv manages an isolated test environment for integration tests.\\n    46→type TestEnv struct {\\n    47→\\tT                *testing.T\\n    48→\\tRepoDir          string\\n    49→\\tClaudeProjectDir string\\n    50→\\tGeminiProjectDir string\\n    51→\\tSessionCounter   int\\n    52→}\\n    53→\\n    54→// NewTestEnv creates a new isolated test environment.\\n    55→// It creates temp directories for the git repo and agent project files.\\n    56→// Note: Does NOT change working directory to allow parallel test execution.\\n    57→// Note: Does NOT use t.Setenv to allow parallel test execution - CLI commands\\n    58→// receive the env var via cmd.Env instead.\\n    59→func NewTestEnv(t *testing.T) *TestEnv {\\n    60→\\tt.Helper()\\n    61→\\n    62→\\t// Resolve symlinks on macOS where /var -> /private/var\\n    63→\\t// This ensures the CLI subprocess and test use consistent paths\\n    64→\\trepoDir := t.TempDir()\\n    65→\\tif resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(repoDir); err == nil {\\n    66→\\t\\trepoDir = resolved\\n    67→\\t}\\n    68→\\tclaudeProjectDir := t.TempDir()\\n    69→\\tif resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(claudeProjectDir); err == nil {\\n    70→\\t\\tclaudeProjectDir = resolved\\n    71→\\t}\\n    72→\\tgeminiProjectDir := t.TempDir()\\n    73→\\tif resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(geminiProjectDir); err == nil {\\n    74→\\t\\tgeminiProjectDir = resolved\\n    75→\\t}\\n    76→\\n    77→\\tenv := &TestEnv{\\n    78→\\t\\tT:                t,\\n    79→\\t\\tRepoDir:          repoDir,\\n    80→\\t\\tClaudeProjectDir: claudeProjectDir,\\n    81→\\t\\tGeminiProjectDir: geminiProjectDir,\\n    82→\\t}\\n    83→\\n    84→\\t// Note: Don't use t.Setenv here - it's incompatible with t.Parallel()\\n    85→\\t// CLI commands receive ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR or ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR via cmd.Env instead\\n    86→\\n    87→\\treturn env\\n    88→}\\n    89→\\n    90→// Cleanup is a no-op retained for backwards compatibility.\\n    91→//\\n    92→// Previously this method restored the working directory after NewTestEnv changed it.\\n    93→// With the refactor to remove os.Chdir from NewTestEnv:\\n    94→// - Temp directories are now cleaned up automatically by t.TempDir()\\n    95→// - Working directory is never changed, so no restoration is needed\\n    96→//\\n    97→// This method is kept to avoid breaking existing tests that call defer env.Cleanup().\\n    98→// New tests should not call this method as it serves no purpose.\\n    99→//\\n   100→// Deprecated: This method is a no-op and will be removed in a future version.\\n   101→func (env *TestEnv) Cleanup() {\\n   102→\\t// No-op - temp dirs are cleaned up by t.TempDir()\\n   103→}\\n   104→\\n   105→// cliEnv returns the environment variables for CLI execution.\\n   106→// Includes both Claude and Gemini project dirs so tests work for any agent.\\n   107→func (env *TestEnv) cliEnv() []string {\\n   108→\\treturn append(os.Environ(),\\n   109→\\t\\t\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR=\\\"+env.ClaudeProjectDir,\\n   110→\\t\\t\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR=\\\"+env.GeminiProjectDir,\\n   111→\\t\\t\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0\\\", // Prevent interactive prompts from blocking in tests\\n   112→\\t)\\n   113→}\\n   114→\\n   115→// RunCLI runs the entire CLI with the given arguments and returns stdout.\\n   116→func (env *TestEnv) RunCLI(args ...string) string {\\n   117→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   118→\\toutput, err := env.RunCLIWithError(args...)\\n   119→\\tif err != nil {\\n   120→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"CLI command failed: %v\\\\nArgs: %v\\\\nOutput: %s\\\", err, args, output)\\n   121→\\t}\\n   122→\\treturn output\\n   123→}\\n   124→\\n   125→// RunCLIWithError runs the entire CLI and returns output and error.\\n   126→func (env *TestEnv) RunCLIWithError(args ...string) (string, error) {\\n   127→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   128→\\n   129→\\t// Run CLI using the shared binary\\n   130→\\tcmd := exec.Command(getTestBinary(), args...)\\n   131→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   132→\\tcmd.Env = env.cliEnv()\\n   133→\\n   134→\\toutput, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\\n   135→\\treturn string(output), err\\n   136→}\\n   137→\\n   138→// RunCLIWithStdin runs the CLI with stdin input.\\n   139→func (env *TestEnv) RunCLIWithStdin(stdin string, args ...string) string {\\n   140→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   141→\\n   142→\\t// Run CLI with stdin using the shared binary\\n   143→\\tcmd := exec.Command(getTestBinary(), args...)\\n   144→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   145→\\tcmd.Env = env.cliEnv()\\n   146→\\tcmd.Stdin = strings.NewReader(stdin)\\n   147→\\n   148→\\toutput, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\\n   149→\\tif err != nil {\\n   150→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"CLI command failed: %v\\\\nArgs: %v\\\\nOutput: %s\\\", err, args, output)\\n   151→\\t}\\n   152→\\treturn string(output)\\n   153→}\\n   154→\\n   155→// NewRepoEnv creates a TestEnv with an initialized git repo and Entire.\\n   156→// This is a convenience factory for tests that need a basic repo setup.\\n   157→func NewRepoEnv(t *testing.T, strategy string) *TestEnv {\\n   158→\\tt.Helper()\\n   159→\\tenv := NewTestEnv(t)\\n   160→\\tenv.InitRepo()\\n   161→\\tenv.InitEntire(strategy)\\n   162→\\treturn env\\n   163→}\\n   164→\\n   165→// NewRepoWithCommit creates a TestEnv with a git repo, Entire, and an initial commit.\\n   166→// The initial commit contains a README.md and .gitignore (excluding .entire/).\\n   167→func NewRepoWithCommit(t *testing.T, strategy string) *TestEnv {\\n   168→\\tt.Helper()\\n   169→\\tenv := NewRepoEnv(t, strategy)\\n   170→\\tenv.WriteFile(\\\".gitignore\\\", \\\".entire/\\\\n\\\")\\n   171→\\tenv.WriteFile(\\\"README.md\\\", \\\"# Test Repository\\\")\\n   172→\\tenv.GitAdd(\\\".gitignore\\\")\\n   173→\\tenv.GitAdd(\\\"README.md\\\")\\n   174→\\tenv.GitCommit(\\\"Initial commit\\\")\\n   175→\\treturn env\\n   176→}\\n   177→\\n   178→// NewFeatureBranchEnv creates a TestEnv ready for session testing.\\n   179→// It initializes the repo, creates an initial commit on main,\\n   180→// and checks out a feature branch. This is the most common setup\\n   181→// for session and rewind tests since Entire tracking skips main/master.\\n   182→func NewFeatureBranchEnv(t *testing.T, strategyName string) *TestEnv {\\n   183→\\tt.Helper()\\n   184→\\tenv := NewRepoWithCommit(t, strategyName)\\n   185→\\tenv.GitCheckoutNewBranch(\\\"feature/test-branch\\\")\\n   186→\\treturn env\\n   187→}\\n   188→\\n   189→// AllStrategies returns all strategy names for parameterized tests.\\n   190→func AllStrategies() []string {\\n   191→\\treturn []string{\\n   192→\\t\\tstrategy.StrategyNameAutoCommit,\\n   193→\\t\\tstrategy.StrategyNameManualCommit,\\n   194→\\t}\\n   195→}\\n   196→\\n   197→// RunForAllStrategies runs a test function for each strategy in parallel.\\n   198→// This reduces boilerplate for tests that need to verify behavior across all strategies.\\n   199→// Each subtest gets its own TestEnv with a feature branch ready for testing.\\n   200→func RunForAllStrategies(t *testing.T, testFn func(t *testing.T, env *TestEnv, strategyName string)) {\\n   201→\\tt.Helper()\\n   202→\\tfor _, strat := range AllStrategies() {\\n   203→\\t\\tstrat := strat // capture for parallel\\n   204→\\t\\tt.Run(strat, func(t *testing.T) {\\n   205→\\t\\t\\tt.Parallel()\\n   206→\\t\\t\\tenv := NewFeatureBranchEnv(t, strat)\\n   207→\\t\\t\\ttestFn(t, env, strat)\\n   208→\\t\\t})\\n   209→\\t}\\n   210→}\\n   211→\\n   212→// RunForAllStrategiesWithRepoEnv runs a test function for each strategy in parallel,\\n   213→// using NewRepoWithCommit instead of NewFeatureBranchEnv. Use this for tests\\n   214→// that need to test behavior on the main branch.\\n   215→func RunForAllStrategiesWithRepoEnv(t *testing.T, testFn func(t *testing.T, env *TestEnv, strategyName string)) {\\n   216→\\tt.Helper()\\n   217→\\tfor _, strat := range AllStrategies() {\\n   218→\\t\\tstrat := strat // capture for parallel\\n   219→\\t\\tt.Run(strat, func(t *testing.T) {\\n   220→\\t\\t\\tt.Parallel()\\n   221→\\t\\t\\tenv := NewRepoWithCommit(t, strat)\\n   222→\\t\\t\\ttestFn(t, env, strat)\\n   223→\\t\\t})\\n   224→\\t}\\n   225→}\\n   226→\\n   227→// RunForAllStrategiesWithBasicEnv runs a test function for each strategy in parallel,\\n   228→// using NewRepoEnv (git repo + entire init, no commits). Use this for tests\\n   229→// that need to verify basic initialization behavior.\\n   230→func RunForAllStrategiesWithBasicEnv(t *testing.T, testFn func(t *testing.T, env *TestEnv, strategyName string)) {\\n   231→\\tt.Helper()\\n   232→\\tfor _, strat := range AllStrategies() {\\n   233→\\t\\tstrat := strat // capture for parallel\\n   234→\\t\\tt.Run(strat, func(t *testing.T) {\\n   235→\\t\\t\\tt.Parallel()\\n   236→\\t\\t\\tenv := NewRepoEnv(t, strat)\\n   237→\\t\\t\\ttestFn(t, env, strat)\\n   238→\\t\\t})\\n   239→\\t}\\n   240→}\\n   241→\\n   242→// RunForStrategiesSequential runs a test function for specific strategies sequentially.\\n   243→// Use this for tests that cannot be parallelized (e.g., tests using os.Chdir).\\n   244→// The strategies parameter allows testing a subset of strategies.\\n   245→func RunForStrategiesSequential(t *testing.T, strategies []string, testFn func(t *testing.T, strategyName string)) {\\n   246→\\tt.Helper()\\n   247→\\tfor _, strat := range strategies {\\n   248→\\t\\tt.Run(strat, func(t *testing.T) {\\n   249→\\t\\t\\ttestFn(t, strat)\\n   250→\\t\\t})\\n   251→\\t}\\n   252→}\\n   253→\\n   254→// InitRepo initializes a git repository in the test environment.\\n   255→func (env *TestEnv) InitRepo() {\\n   256→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   257→\\n   258→\\trepo, err := git.PlainInit(env.RepoDir, false)\\n   259→\\tif err != nil {\\n   260→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to init git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   261→\\t}\\n   262→\\n   263→\\t// Configure git user for commits\\n   264→\\tcfg, err := repo.Config()\\n   265→\\tif err != nil {\\n   266→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get repo config: %v\\\", err)\\n   267→\\t}\\n   268→\\tcfg.User.Name = \\\"Test User\\\"\\n   269→\\tcfg.User.Email = \\\"test@example.com\\\"\\n   270→\\n   271→\\t// Disable GPG signing for test commits (prevents failures if user has commit.gpgsign=true globally)\\n   272→\\tif cfg.Raw == nil {\\n   273→\\t\\tcfg.Raw = config.New()\\n   274→\\t}\\n   275→\\tcfg.Raw.Section(\\\"commit\\\").SetOption(\\\"gpgsign\\\", \\\"false\\\")\\n   276→\\n   277→\\tif err := repo.SetConfig(cfg); err != nil {\\n   278→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to set repo config: %v\\\", err)\\n   279→\\t}\\n   280→}\\n   281→\\n   282→// InitEntire initializes the .entire directory with the specified strategy.\\n   283→func (env *TestEnv) InitEntire(strategyName string) {\\n   284→\\tenv.InitEntireWithOptions(strategyName, nil)\\n   285→}\\n   286→\\n   287→// InitEntireWithOptions initializes the .entire directory with the specified strategy and options.\\n   288→func (env *TestEnv) InitEntireWithOptions(strategyName string, strategyOptions map[string]any) {\\n   289→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   290→\\tenv.initEntireInternal(strategyName, \\\"\\\", strategyOptions)\\n   291→}\\n   292→\\n   293→// InitEntireWithAgent initializes an Entire test environment with a specific agent.\\n   294→// If agentName is empty, defaults to claude-code.\\n   295→func (env *TestEnv) InitEntireWithAgent(strategyName string, agentName agent.AgentName) {\\n   296→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   297→\\tenv.initEntireInternal(strategyName, agentName, nil)\\n   298→}\\n   299→\\n   300→// InitEntireWithAgentAndOptions initializes Entire with the specified strategy, agent, and options.\\n   301→func (env *TestEnv) InitEntireWithAgentAndOptions(strategyName string, agentName agent.AgentName, strategyOptions map[string]any) {\\n   302→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   303→\\tenv.initEntireInternal(strategyName, agentName, strategyOptions)\\n   304→}\\n   305→\\n   306→// initEntireInternal is the common implementation for InitEntire variants.\\n   307→func (env *TestEnv) initEntireInternal(strategyName string, agentName agent.AgentName, strategyOptions map[string]any) {\\n   308→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   309→\\n   310→\\t// Create .entire directory structure\\n   311→\\tentireDir := filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \\\".entire\\\")\\n   312→\\tif err := os.MkdirAll(entireDir, 0o755); err != nil {\\n   313→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to create .entire directory: %v\\\", err)\\n   314→\\t}\\n   315→\\n   316→\\t// Create tmp directory\\n   317→\\ttmpDir := filepath.Join(entireDir, \\\"tmp\\\")\\n   318→\\tif err := os.MkdirAll(tmpDir, 0o755); err != nil {\\n   319→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to create .entire/tmp directory: %v\\\", err)\\n   320→\\t}\\n   321→\\n   322→\\t// Write settings.json\\n   323→\\tsettings := map[string]any{\\n   324→\\t\\t\\\"strategy\\\":  strategyName,\\n   325→\\t\\t\\\"local_dev\\\": true, // Note: git-triggered hooks won't work (path is relative); tests call hooks via getTestBinary() instead\\n   326→\\t}\\n   327→\\t// Only add agent if specified (otherwise defaults to claude-code)\\n   328→\\tif agentName != \\\"\\\" {\\n   329→\\t\\tsettings[\\\"agent\\\"] = string(agentName)\\n   330→\\t}\\n   331→\\tif strategyOptions != nil {\\n   332→\\t\\tsettings[\\\"strategy_options\\\"] = strategyOptions\\n   333→\\t}\\n   334→\\tdata, err := jsonutil.MarshalIndentWithNewline(settings, \\\"\\\", \\\"  \\\")\\n   335→\\tif err != nil {\\n   336→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to marshal settings: %v\\\", err)\\n   337→\\t}\\n   338→\\tsettingsPath := filepath.Join(entireDir, paths.SettingsFileName)\\n   339→\\tif err := os.WriteFile(settingsPath, data, 0o644); err != nil {\\n   340→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to write %s: %v\\\", paths.SettingsFileName, err)\\n   341→\\t}\\n   342→}\\n   343→\\n   344→// WriteFile creates a file with the given content in the test repo.\\n   345→// It creates parent directories as needed.\\n   346→func (env *TestEnv) WriteFile(path, content string) {\\n   347→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   348→\\n   349→\\tfullPath := filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, path)\\n   350→\\n   351→\\t// Create parent directories\\n   352→\\tdir := filepath.Dir(fullPath)\\n   353→\\tif err := os.MkdirAll(dir, 0o755); err != nil {\\n   354→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to create directory %s: %v\\\", dir, err)\\n   355→\\t}\\n   356→\\n   357→\\tif err := os.WriteFile(fullPath, []byte(content), 0o644); err != nil {\\n   358→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to write file %s: %v\\\", path, err)\\n   359→\\t}\\n   360→}\\n   361→\\n   362→// ReadFile reads a file from the test repo.\\n   363→func (env *TestEnv) ReadFile(path string) string {\\n   364→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   365→\\n   366→\\tfullPath := filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, path)\\n   367→\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(fullPath)\\n   368→\\tif err != nil {\\n   369→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to read file %s: %v\\\", path, err)\\n   370→\\t}\\n   371→\\treturn string(data)\\n   372→}\\n   373→\\n   374→// ReadFileAbsolute reads a file using an absolute path.\\n   375→func (env *TestEnv) ReadFileAbsolute(path string) string {\\n   376→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   377→\\n   378→\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\\n   379→\\tif err != nil {\\n   380→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to read file %s: %v\\\", path, err)\\n   381→\\t}\\n   382→\\treturn string(data)\\n   383→}\\n   384→\\n   385→// FileExists checks if a file exists in the test repo.\\n   386→func (env *TestEnv) FileExists(path string) bool {\\n   387→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   388→\\n   389→\\tfullPath := filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, path)\\n   390→\\t_, err := os.Stat(fullPath)\\n   391→\\treturn err == nil\\n   392→}\\n   393→\\n   394→// GitAdd stages files for commit.\\n   395→func (env *TestEnv) GitAdd(paths ...string) {\\n   396→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   397→\\n   398→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   399→\\tif err != nil {\\n   400→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   401→\\t}\\n   402→\\n   403→\\tworktree, err := repo.Worktree()\\n   404→\\tif err != nil {\\n   405→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree: %v\\\", err)\\n   406→\\t}\\n   407→\\n   408→\\tfor _, path := range paths {\\n   409→\\t\\tif _, err := worktree.Add(path); err != nil {\\n   410→\\t\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to add file %s: %v\\\", path, err)\\n   411→\\t\\t}\\n   412→\\t}\\n   413→}\\n   414→\\n   415→// GitCommit creates a commit with all staged files.\\n   416→func (env *TestEnv) GitCommit(message string) {\\n   417→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   418→\\n   419→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   420→\\tif err != nil {\\n   421→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   422→\\t}\\n   423→\\n   424→\\tworktree, err := repo.Worktree()\\n   425→\\tif err != nil {\\n   426→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree: %v\\\", err)\\n   427→\\t}\\n   428→\\n   429→\\t_, err = worktree.Commit(message, &git.CommitOptions{\\n   430→\\t\\tAuthor: &object.Signature{\\n   431→\\t\\t\\tName:  \\\"Test User\\\",\\n   432→\\t\\t\\tEmail: \\\"test@example.com\\\",\\n   433→\\t\\t\\tWhen:  time.Now(),\\n   434→\\t\\t},\\n   435→\\t})\\n   436→\\tif err != nil {\\n   437→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to commit: %v\\\", err)\\n   438→\\t}\\n   439→}\\n   440→\\n   441→// GitCommitWithMetadata creates a commit with Entire-Metadata trailer.\\n   442→// This simulates commits created by the commit strategy.\\n   443→func (env *TestEnv) GitCommitWithMetadata(message, metadataDir string) {\\n   444→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   445→\\n   446→\\t// Format message with metadata trailer\\n   447→\\tfullMessage := message + \\\"\\\\n\\\\nEntire-Metadata: \\\" + metadataDir + \\\"\\\\n\\\"\\n   448→\\n   449→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   450→\\tif err != nil {\\n   451→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   452→\\t}\\n   453→\\n   454→\\tworktree, err := repo.Worktree()\\n   455→\\tif err != nil {\\n   456→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree: %v\\\", err)\\n   457→\\t}\\n   458→\\n   459→\\t_, err = worktree.Commit(fullMessage, &git.CommitOptions{\\n   460→\\t\\tAuthor: &object.Signature{\\n   461→\\t\\t\\tName:  \\\"Test User\\\",\\n   462→\\t\\t\\tEmail: \\\"test@example.com\\\",\\n   463→\\t\\t\\tWhen:  time.Now(),\\n   464→\\t\\t},\\n   465→\\t})\\n   466→\\tif err != nil {\\n   467→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to commit: %v\\\", err)\\n   468→\\t}\\n   469→}\\n   470→\\n   471→// GitCommitWithCheckpointID creates a commit with Entire-Checkpoint trailer.\\n   472→// This simulates commits created by the auto-commit strategy.\\n   473→func (env *TestEnv) GitCommitWithCheckpointID(message, checkpointID string) {\\n   474→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   475→\\n   476→\\t// Format message with checkpoint trailer\\n   477→\\tfullMessage := message + \\\"\\\\n\\\\nEntire-Checkpoint: \\\" + checkpointID + \\\"\\\\n\\\"\\n   478→\\n   479→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   480→\\tif err != nil {\\n   481→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   482→\\t}\\n   483→\\n   484→\\tworktree, err := repo.Worktree()\\n   485→\\tif err != nil {\\n   486→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree: %v\\\", err)\\n   487→\\t}\\n   488→\\n   489→\\t_, err = worktree.Commit(fullMessage, &git.CommitOptions{\\n   490→\\t\\tAuthor: &object.Signature{\\n   491→\\t\\t\\tName:  \\\"Test User\\\",\\n   492→\\t\\t\\tEmail: \\\"test@example.com\\\",\\n   493→\\t\\t\\tWhen:  time.Now(),\\n   494→\\t\\t},\\n   495→\\t})\\n   496→\\tif err != nil {\\n   497→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to commit: %v\\\", err)\\n   498→\\t}\\n   499→}\\n   500→\\n   501→// GitCommitWithMultipleSessions creates a commit with multiple Entire-Session trailers.\\n   502→// This simulates merge commits that combine work from multiple sessions.\\n   503→func (env *TestEnv) GitCommitWithMultipleSessions(message string, sessionIDs []string) {\\n   504→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   505→\\n   506→\\t// Format message with multiple session trailers\\n   507→\\tfullMessage := message + \\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n   508→\\tvar fullMessageSb404 strings.Builder\\n   509→\\tfor _, sessionID := range sessionIDs {\\n   510→\\t\\tfullMessageSb404.WriteString(\\\"Entire-Session: \\\" + sessionID + \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n   511→\\t}\\n   512→\\tfullMessage += fullMessageSb404.String()\\n   513→\\n   514→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   515→\\tif err != nil {\\n   516→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   517→\\t}\\n   518→\\n   519→\\tworktree, err := repo.Worktree()\\n   520→\\tif err != nil {\\n   521→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree: %v\\\", err)\\n   522→\\t}\\n   523→\\n   524→\\t_, err = worktree.Commit(fullMessage, &git.CommitOptions{\\n   525→\\t\\tAuthor: &object.Signature{\\n   526→\\t\\t\\tName:  \\\"Test User\\\",\\n   527→\\t\\t\\tEmail: \\\"test@example.com\\\",\\n   528→\\t\\t\\tWhen:  time.Now(),\\n   529→\\t\\t},\\n   530→\\t})\\n   531→\\tif err != nil {\\n   532→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to commit: %v\\\", err)\\n   533→\\t}\\n   534→}\\n   535→\\n   536→// GetHeadHash returns the current HEAD commit hash.\\n   537→func (env *TestEnv) GetHeadHash() string {\\n   538→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   539→\\n   540→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   541→\\tif err != nil {\\n   542→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   543→\\t}\\n   544→\\n   545→\\thead, err := repo.Head()\\n   546→\\tif err != nil {\\n   547→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get HEAD: %v\\\", err)\\n   548→\\t}\\n   549→\\n   550→\\treturn head.Hash().String()\\n   551→}\\n   552→\\n   553→// GetShadowBranchName returns the worktree-specific shadow branch name for the current HEAD.\\n   554→// Format: entire/<commit[:7]>-<hash(worktreeID)[:6]>\\n   555→func (env *TestEnv) GetShadowBranchName() string {\\n   556→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   557→\\n   558→\\theadHash := env.GetHeadHash()\\n   559→\\tworktreeID, err := paths.GetWorktreeID(env.RepoDir)\\n   560→\\tif err != nil {\\n   561→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree ID: %v\\\", err)\\n   562→\\t}\\n   563→\\treturn checkpoint.ShadowBranchNameForCommit(headHash, worktreeID)\\n   564→}\\n   565→\\n   566→// GetShadowBranchNameForCommit returns the worktree-specific shadow branch name for a given commit.\\n   567→// Format: entire/<commit[:7]>-<hash(worktreeID)[:6]>\\n   568→func (env *TestEnv) GetShadowBranchNameForCommit(commitHash string) string {\\n   569→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   570→\\n   571→\\tworktreeID, err := paths.GetWorktreeID(env.RepoDir)\\n   572→\\tif err != nil {\\n   573→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get worktree ID: %v\\\", err)\\n   574→\\t}\\n   575→\\treturn checkpoint.ShadowBranchNameForCommit(commitHash, worktreeID)\\n   576→}\\n   577→\\n   578→// GetGitLog returns a list of commit hashes from HEAD.\\n   579→func (env *TestEnv) GetGitLog() []string {\\n   580→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   581→\\n   582→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   583→\\tif err != nil {\\n   584→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   585→\\t}\\n   586→\\n   587→\\thead, err := repo.Head()\\n   588→\\tif err != nil {\\n   589→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get HEAD: %v\\\", err)\\n   590→\\t}\\n   591→\\n   592→\\tcommitIter, err := repo.Log(&git.LogOptions{From: head.Hash()})\\n   593→\\tif err != nil {\\n   594→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get log: %v\\\", err)\\n   595→\\t}\\n   596→\\n   597→\\tvar commits []string\\n   598→\\terr = commitIter.ForEach(func(c *object.Commit) error {\\n   599→\\t\\tcommits = append(commits, c.Hash.String())\\n   600→\\t\\treturn nil\\n   601→\\t})\\n   602→\\tif err != nil {\\n   603→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to iterate commits: %v\\\", err)\\n   604→\\t}\\n   605→\\n   606→\\treturn commits\\n   607→}\\n   608→\\n   609→// GitCheckoutNewBranch creates and checks out a new branch.\\n   610→// Uses git CLI instead of go-git to work around go-git v5 bug where Checkout\\n   611→// deletes untracked files (see https://github.com/go-git/go-git/issues/970).\\n   612→func (env *TestEnv) GitCheckoutNewBranch(branchName string) {\\n   613→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   614→\\n   615→\\tcmd := exec.Command(\\\"git\\\", \\\"checkout\\\", \\\"-b\\\", branchName)\\n   616→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   617→\\tif output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {\\n   618→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to checkout new branch %s: %v\\\\nOutput: %s\\\", branchName, err, output)\\n   619→\\t}\\n   620→}\\n   621→\\n   622→// GetCurrentBranch returns the current branch name.\\n   623→func (env *TestEnv) GetCurrentBranch() string {\\n   624→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   625→\\n   626→\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpen(env.RepoDir)\\n   627→\\tif err != nil {\\n   628→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to open git repo: %v\\\", err)\\n   629→\\t}\\n   630→\\n   631→\\thead, err := repo.Head()\\n   632→\\tif err != nil {\\n   633→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to get HEAD: %v\\\", err)\\n   634→\\t}\\n   635→\\n   636→\\tif !head.Name().IsBranch() {\\n   637→\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\" // Detached HEAD\\n   638→\\t}\\n   639→\\n   640→\\treturn head.Name().Short()\\n   641→}\\n   642→\\n   643→// RewindPoint mirrors strategy.RewindPoint for test assertions.\\n   644→type RewindPoint struct {\\n   645→\\tID               string\\n   646→\\tMessage          string\\n   647→\\tMetadataDir      string\\n   648→\\tDate             time.Time\\n   649→\\tIsTaskCheckpoint bool\\n   650→\\tToolUseID        string\\n   651→\\tIsLogsOnly       bool\\n   652→\\tCondensationID   string\\n   653→}\\n   654→\\n   655→// GetRewindPoints returns available rewind points using the CLI.\\n   656→func (env *TestEnv) GetRewindPoints() []RewindPoint {\\n   657→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   658→\\n   659→\\t// Run rewind --list using the shared binary\\n   660→\\tcmd := exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"rewind\\\", \\\"--list\\\")\\n   661→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   662→\\tcmd.Env = env.cliEnv()\\n   663→\\n   664→\\toutput, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\\n   665→\\tif err != nil {\\n   666→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"rewind --list failed: %v\\\\nOutput: %s\\\", err, output)\\n   667→\\t}\\n   668→\\n   669→\\t// Parse JSON output\\n   670→\\tvar jsonPoints []struct {\\n   671→\\t\\tID               string `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n   672→\\t\\tMessage          string `json:\\\"message\\\"`\\n   673→\\t\\tMetadataDir      string `json:\\\"metadata_dir\\\"`\\n   674→\\t\\tDate             string `json:\\\"date\\\"`\\n   675→\\t\\tIsTaskCheckpoint bool   `json:\\\"is_task_checkpoint\\\"`\\n   676→\\t\\tToolUseID        string `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"`\\n   677→\\t\\tIsLogsOnly       bool   `json:\\\"is_logs_only\\\"`\\n   678→\\t\\tCondensationID   string `json:\\\"condensation_id\\\"`\\n   679→\\t}\\n   680→\\n   681→\\tif err := json.Unmarshal(output, &jsonPoints); err != nil {\\n   682→\\t\\tenv.T.Fatalf(\\\"failed to parse rewind points: %v\\\\nOutput: %s\\\", err, output)\\n   683→\\t}\\n   684→\\n   685→\\tpoints := make([]RewindPoint, len(jsonPoints))\\n   686→\\tfor i, jp := range jsonPoints {\\n   687→\\t\\tdate, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, jp.Date)\\n   688→\\t\\tpoints[i] = RewindPoint{\\n   689→\\t\\t\\tID:               jp.ID,\\n   690→\\t\\t\\tMessage:          jp.Message,\\n   691→\\t\\t\\tMetadataDir:      jp.MetadataDir,\\n   692→\\t\\t\\tDate:             date,\\n   693→\\t\\t\\tIsTaskCheckpoint: jp.IsTaskCheckpoint,\\n   694→\\t\\t\\tToolUseID:        jp.ToolUseID,\\n   695→\\t\\t\\tIsLogsOnly:       jp.IsLogsOnly,\\n   696→\\t\\t\\tCondensationID:   jp.CondensationID,\\n   697→\\t\\t}\\n   698→\\t}\\n   699→\\n   700→\\treturn points\\n   701→}\\n   702→\\n   703→// Rewind performs a rewind to the specified commit ID using the CLI.\\n   704→func (env *TestEnv) Rewind(commitID string) error {\\n   705→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   706→\\n   707→\\t// Run rewind --to <commitID> using the shared binary\\n   708→\\tcmd := exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"rewind\\\", \\\"--to\\\", commitID)\\n   709→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   710→\\tcmd.Env = env.cliEnv()\\n   711→\\n   712→\\toutput, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\\n   713→\\tif err != nil {\\n   714→\\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"rewind failed: \\\" + string(output))\\n   715→\\t}\\n   716→\\n   717→\\tenv.T.Logf(\\\"Rewind output: %s\\\", output)\\n   718→\\treturn nil\\n   719→}\\n   720→\\n   721→// RewindLogsOnly performs a logs-only rewind using the CLI.\\n   722→// This restores session logs without modifying the working directory.\\n   723→func (env *TestEnv) RewindLogsOnly(commitID string) error {\\n   724→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   725→\\n   726→\\t// Run rewind --to <commitID> --logs-only using the shared binary\\n   727→\\tcmd := exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"rewind\\\", \\\"--to\\\", commitID, \\\"--logs-only\\\")\\n   728→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   729→\\tcmd.Env = env.cliEnv()\\n   730→\\n   731→\\toutput, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\\n   732→\\tif err != nil {\\n   733→\\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"rewind logs-only failed: \\\" + string(output))\\n   734→\\t}\\n   735→\\n   736→\\tenv.T.Logf(\\\"Rewind logs-only output: %s\\\", output)\\n   737→\\treturn nil\\n   738→}\\n   739→\\n   740→// RewindReset performs a reset rewind using the CLI.\\n   741→// This resets the branch to the specified commit (destructive).\\n   742→func (env *TestEnv) RewindReset(commitID string) error {\\n   743→\\tenv.T.Helper()\\n   744→\\n   745→\\t// Run rewind --to <commitID> --reset using the shared binary\\n   746→\\tcmd := exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"rewind\\\", \\\"--to\\\", commitID, \\\"--reset\\\")\\n   747→\\tcmd.Dir = env.RepoDir\\n   748→\\