gent gemini` (adds hooks, preserves settings).\\n- `hooks.go` — Has `HookRunner` (claude-code) and `GeminiHookRunner` with simulation methods. No `FactoryDroidHookRunner`.\\n\\n### Factory AI Droid agent capabilities:\\n- **Registered as** `\\\"factoryai-droid\\\"` (`agent.AgentNameFactoryAIDroid`)\\n- **Implements**: `agent.Agent`, `agent.HookSupport`, `agent.HookHandler`, `agent.TranscriptAnalyzer`, `agent.TokenCalculator`, `agent.SubagentAwareExtractor`\\n- **HookSupport**: `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, `AreHooksInstalled` (writes to `.factory/settings.json`)\\n- **InstallHooks** installs 7 hooks: SessionStart, SessionEnd, Stop, UserPromptSubmit, PreToolUse[Task], PostToolUse[Task], PreCompact\\n- **Hook command format**: `entire hooks factoryai-droid <verb>` (prod) or `go run ${FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks factoryai-droid <verb>` (localDev)\\n- **Permissions deny rule**: `Read(./.entire/metadata/**)`\\n- **ParseHookInput**: Maps `session_id` → `SessionID`, `transcript_path` → `SessionRef`\\n- **Transcript format**: JSONL (same as Claude Code, NOT JSON like Gemini)\\n- **Session stubs**: GetSessionDir, ReadSession, WriteSession all return \\\"not implemented\\\" errors\\n- **FormatResumeCommand**: `\\\"droid --session-id \\\" + sessionID`\\n- **DetectPresence**: checks for `.factory` directory\\n- **ProtectedDirs**: `[\\\".factory\\\"]`\\n- **GetHookConfigPath**: `.factory/settings.json`\\n\\n### Key differences from Gemini:\\n- Uses JSONL transcript format (like Claude Code), not JSON\\n- Hook structure uses `FactoryHookMatcher` with `matcher` + `hooks` array (similar to Claude but with Factory-specific hook types like `PreCompact`)\\n- ReadSession/WriteSession/GetSessionDir are not yet implemented (stubs that return errors)\\n- Hook runner commands go to `entire hooks factoryai-droid <verb>` instead of `entire hooks gemini <verb>`\\n\\n## What to create:\\n\\n### 1. Add to `agent_test.go` (following existing patterns):\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidAgentDetection** — Mirror of `TestGeminiCLIAgentDetection`\\n- Subtest: \\\"factoryai-droid agent is registered\\\" — `agent.List()` contains \\\"factoryai-droid\\\" \\n- Subtest: \\\"factoryai-droid detects presence when .factory exists\\\" — os.Chdir, create `.factory` dir, DetectPresence returns true\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidHookInstallation** — Mirror of `TestGeminiCLIHookInstallation`  \\n- Subtest: \\\"installs all required hooks\\\" — InstallHooks(false, false) returns 7, AreHooksInstalled() true, settings.json contains all hook types\\n- Subtest: \\\"idempotent - second install returns 0\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"localDev mode uses go run\\\" — settings.json contains \\\"go run\\\" and \\\"${FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR}\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"production mode uses entire binary\\\" — settings.json contains \\\"entire hooks factoryai-droid\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"force flag reinstalls hooks\\\" — force=true returns 7 after initial install\\n- Subtest: \\\"adds permissions.deny rule\\\" — settings.json has `Read(./.entire/metadata/**)`\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidHelperMethods** — Mirror of `TestGeminiCLIHelperMethods`\\n- Subtest: \\\"FormatResumeCommand returns droid --session-id\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"GetHookConfigPath returns .factory/settings.json\\\"\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidSessionStubs** — Unique to Factory AI Droid (since ReadSession/WriteSession are stubs)\\n- Subtest: \\\"ReadSession returns not-implemented error\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"WriteSession returns not-implemented error\\\"\\n- Subtest: \\\"GetSessionDir returns not-implemented error\\\"\\n\\n### 2. Create `setup_factoryai_hooks_test.go` (mirror of `setup_gemini_hooks_test.go`):\\n\\n**TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_AddsAllRequiredHooks** — Smoke test for `entire enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Creates env, InitRepo, InitEntire, creates initial commit\\n- Runs `enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Verifies `.factory/settings.json` contains all 7 hook types\\n- Verifies permissions.deny rule\\n\\n**TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_PreservesExistingSettings** — Preserves custom settings\\n- Pre-populates `.factory/settings.json` with custom fields and user hooks\\n- Runs enable\\n- Verifies custom fields and user hooks preserved, our hooks added\\n\\n### 3. Add `FactoryDroidHookRunner` to `hooks.go`:\\n\\nA hook runner that simulates Factory AI Droid hooks, similar to `GeminiHookRunner`:\\n- `NewFactoryDroidHookRunner(repoDir string, t TestT) *FactoryDroidHookRunner`\\n- `SimulateUserPromptSubmit(sessionID string) error` — runs `entire hooks factoryai-droid user-prompt-submit`\\n- `SimulateStop(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error` — runs `entire hooks factoryai-droid stop`\\n- `SimulateSessionEnd(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error`\\n- `SimulatePreTask(sessionID, transcriptPath, toolUseID string) error`\\n- `SimulatePostTask(input PostTaskInput) error`\\n- Convenience methods on TestEnv: `SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmit`, `SimulateFactoryDroidStop`, etc.\\n\\nAlso add `FactoryDroidSession` struct and `NewFactoryDroidSession()` on TestEnv that creates sessions with JSONL transcripts.\\n\\n### 4. Add Factory AI Droid to `agent_strategy_test.go`:\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidAgentStrategyComposition** — Same as `TestAgentStrategyComposition` but using factoryai-droid agent. Since ReadSession returns \\\"not implemented\\\", this test should verify checkpoints work through the hook-based flow (UserPromptSubmit → Stop).\\n\\nNote: Since ReadSession is a stub, the strategy tests that depend on ReadSession (like transcript restoration) should be skipped or tested differently for Factory AI Droid.\\n\\n## Important considerations:\\n- Factory AI Droid uses the same JSONL transcript format as Claude Code, so the existing `TranscriptBuilder` and `NewSession` should work for creating test transcripts\\n- Tests that use `os.Chdir` cannot be parallel\\n- All other tests should use `t.Parallel()`\\n- Hook simulation runs the CLI binary via `exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"hooks\\\", \\\"factoryai-droid\\\", hookName)`\\n- The Factory AI Droid hooks don't need a project dir env var like Claude/Gemini (no `ENTIRE_TEST_FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR` needed since the agent doesn't use one for session resolution)\",\"agentId\":\"a9868ef\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_012zqVgRP1cccpT7yr9kEc2x\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016NtmS9a4tieVSYn3iCqNek\",\"uuid\":\"24dfab08-6449-4ea0-bc37-02cbe7c5d9fc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T21:45:52.164Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"24dfab08-6449-4ea0-bc37-02cbe7c5d9fc\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d4e06782-5186-4133-bb90-098cac18412b\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"quiet-forging-kettle\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Task\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016NtmS9a4tieVSYn3iCqNek\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_016NtmS9a4tieVSYn3iCqNek\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T21:47:33.249Z\",\"uuid\":\"0b9b06ca-8479-488b-8827-ee856332ee7c\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"06765447-0390-40ee-86ab-d0232cb5967c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d4e06782-5186-4133-bb90-098cac18412b\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"quiet-forging-kettle\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_016NtmS9a4tieVSYn3iCqNek\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a complete picture. Let me present the detailed implementation plan.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation Plan: Factory AI Droid Integration Tests\\n\\n### Overview\\n\\nThe goal is to add comprehensive integration tests for the Factory AI Droid agent, mirroring the patterns established for Claude Code and Gemini CLI. This involves modifying 3 