ctoryai_hooks_test.go` (mirror of `setup_gemini_hooks_test.go`):\\n\\n**TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_AddsAllRequiredHooks** — Smoke test for `entire enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Creates env, InitRepo, InitEntire, creates initial commit\\n- Runs `enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Verifies `.factory/settings.json` contains all 7 hook types\\n- Verifies permissions.deny rule\\n\\n**TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_PreservesExistingSettings** — Preserves custom settings\\n- Pre-populates `.factory/settings.json` with custom fields and user hooks\\n- Runs enable\\n- Verifies custom fields and user hooks preserved, our hooks added\\n\\n### 3. Add `FactoryDroidHookRunner` to `hooks.go`:\\n\\nA hook runner that simulates Factory AI Droid hooks, similar to `GeminiHookRunner`:\\n- `NewFactoryDroidHookRunner(repoDir string, t TestT) *FactoryDroidHookRunner`\\n- `SimulateUserPromptSubmit(sessionID string) error` — runs `entire hooks factoryai-droid user-prompt-submit`\\n- `SimulateStop(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error` — runs `entire hooks factoryai-droid stop`\\n- `SimulateSessionEnd(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error`\\n- `SimulatePreTask(sessionID, transcriptPath, toolUseID string) error`\\n- `SimulatePostTask(input PostTaskInput) error`\\n- Convenience methods on TestEnv: `SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmit`, `SimulateFactoryDroidStop`, etc.\\n\\nAlso add `FactoryDroidSession` struct and `NewFactoryDroidSession()` on TestEnv that creates sessions with JSONL transcripts.\\n\\n### 4. Add Factory AI Droid to `agent_strategy_test.go`:\\n\\n**TestFactoryAIDroidAgentStrategyComposition** — Same as `TestAgentStrategyComposition` but using factoryai-droid agent. Since ReadSession returns \\\"not implemented\\\", this test should verify checkpoints work through the hook-based flow (UserPromptSubmit → Stop).\\n\\nNote: Since ReadSession is a stub, the strategy tests that depend on ReadSession (like transcript restoration) should be skipped or tested differently for Factory AI Droid.\\n\\n## Important considerations:\\n- Factory AI Droid uses the same JSONL transcript format as Claude Code, so the existing `TranscriptBuilder` and `NewSession` should work for creating test transcripts\\n- Tests that use `os.Chdir` cannot be parallel\\n- All other tests should use `t.Parallel()`\\n- Hook simulation runs the CLI binary via `exec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"hooks\\\", \\\"factoryai-droid\\\", hookName)`\\n- The Factory AI Droid hooks don't need a project dir env var like Claude/Gemini (no `ENTIRE_TEST_FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR` needed since the agent doesn't use one for session resolution)\",\"agentId\":\"a9868ef\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a complete picture. Let me present the detailed implementation plan.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation Plan: Factory AI Droid Integration Tests\\n\\n### Overview\\n\\nThe goal is to add comprehensive integration tests for the Factory AI Droid agent, mirroring the patterns established for Claude Code and Gemini CLI. This involves modifying 3 existing files and creating 1 new file in `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/`.\\n\\n### Key Design Observations\\n\\n**Droid transcript format is different from both Claude Code and Gemini.** Factory AI Droid uses a wrapped JSONL format where each line has `{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant|user\\\",\\\"content\\\":[...]}}`. The existing `TranscriptBuilder` in `transcript.go` produces Claude Code format (`{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"uuid\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":\\\"...\\\"}}`). For Droid integration tests, a new `DroidTranscriptBuilder` is needed that generates the Droid envelope format.\\n\\n**ReadSession/WriteSession/GetSessionDir are stubs.** These return \\\"not implemented\\\" errors. This means agent+strategy composition tests cannot go through `ag.ReadSession()`. Instead, they must rely entirely on the hook-based flow (UserPromptSubmit, Stop) where the lifecycle dispatcher reads the transcript directly via the `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface.\\n\\n**Hook routing uses `entire hooks factoryai-droid <verb>`.** The hook runner needs to route commands to `\\\"hooks\\\", \\\"factoryai-droid\\\", hookName` (not `\\\"hooks\\\", \\\"claude-code\\\"` or `\\\"hooks\\\", \\\"gemini\\\"`).\\n\\n**No project dir env var needed.** Unlike Claude Code (`ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR`) and Gemini (`ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR`), Factory AI Droid does not use a project dir for session resolution. The `GetSessionDir` method is a stub, so there is no env var to pass.\\n\\n### File-by-File Plan\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 1. Modify `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/hooks.go`\\n\\nAdd `FactoryDroidHookRunner` struct and convenience methods, following the `GeminiHookRunner` pattern.\\n\\n**New types and functions to add:**\\n\\n```go\\n// FactoryDroidHookRunner executes Factory AI Droid hooks in the test environment.\\ntype FactoryDroidHookRunner struct {\\n    RepoDir string\\n    T       TestT  // same interface as HookRunner.T\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe `runFactoryDroidHookInRepoDir` method should execute:\\n```\\nexec.Command(getTestBinary(), \\\"hooks\\\", \\\"factoryai-droid\\\", hookName)\\n```\\nwith `cmd.Dir = r.RepoDir`, `cmd.Stdin = bytes.NewReader(inputJSON)`, and `cmd.Env = os.Environ()` (no special project dir env var needed).\\n\\n**Hook simulation methods on `FactoryDroidHookRunner`:**\\n\\n- `SimulateUserPromptSubmit(sessionID string) error` -- sends `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"prompt\\\":\\\"test prompt\\\"}`\\n- `SimulateStop(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error` -- sends `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"...\\\"}`\\n- `SimulateSessionStart(sessionID string) error` -- sends `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"\\\"}`\\n- `SimulateSessionEnd(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error` -- sends `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"...\\\"}`\\n- `SimulatePreTask(sessionID, transcriptPath, toolUseID string) error` -- sends `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"tool_use_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"tool_input\\\":{}}`\\n- `SimulatePostTask(input PostTaskInput) error` -- sends full post-task input with `tool_response.agentId`\\n- `SimulatePreCompact(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error` -- sends `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"...\\\"}`\\n\\n**Output variants:**\\n- `SimulateUserPromptSubmitWithOutput(sessionID string) HookOutput`\\n- `SimulateSessionStartWithOutput(sessionID string) HookOutput`\\n\\n**FactoryDroidSession struct:**\\n\\n```go\\ntype FactoryDroidSession struct {\\n    ID             string\\n    TranscriptPath string\\n    env            *TestEnv\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**`NewFactoryDroidSession()` on TestEnv** -- creates a session with a `.jsonl` transcript path in `.entire/tmp/`, incrementing `SessionCounter`.\\n\\n**`CreateDroidTranscript(prompt string, changes []FileChange) string`** -- builds a JSONL transcript in Droid envelope format. Each line wraps the message as:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"m<n>\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user|assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[...]}}\\n```\\n\\nFor file changes, the content block should use `{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_use\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"toolu_<n>\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Write\\\",\\\"input\\\":{\\\"file_path\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"...\\\"}}`.\\n\\n**Convenience methods on TestEnv:**\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmit(sessionID string) error`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidStop(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidSessionStart(sessionID string) error`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidSessionEnd(sessionID, transcriptPath string) error`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidPreTask(sessionID, transcriptPath, toolUseID string) error`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidPostTask(input PostTaskInput) error`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmitWithOutput(sessionID string) HookOutput`\\n- `SimulateFactoryDroidSessionStartWithOutput(sessionID string) HookOutput`\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 2. Modify `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/agent_test.go`\\n\\nAdd four new test functions at the end of the file. The file will need the import `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"`.\\n\\n**`TestFactoryAIDroidAgentDetection`** (not parallel at top level due to `os.Chdir` subtests):\\n\\n```go\\nt.Run(\\\"factoryai-droid agent is registered\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    // agent.List() contains \\\"factoryai-droid\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"factoryai-droid detects presence when .factory exists\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // Not parallel - uses os.Chdir\\n    // Create env, InitRepo, create .factory dir\\n    // os.Chdir to env.RepoDir\\n    // agent.Get(\\\"factoryai-droid\\\"), DetectPresence() returns true\\n})\\n```\\n\\n**`TestFactoryAIDroidHookInstallation`** (not parallel at top level due to `os.Chdir` subtests):\\n\\n```go\\nt.Run(\\\"installs all required hooks\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // os.Chdir, InstallHooks(false, false), expect count=7\\n    // AreHooksInstalled() true\\n    // Read .factory/settings.json, verify all hook types present:\\n    //   SessionStart, SessionEnd, Stop, UserPromptSubmit, PreToolUse, PostToolUse, PreCompact\\n    // Verify permissions.deny contains \\\"Read(./.entire/metadata/**)\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"idempotent - second install returns 0\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // First install, second install returns count=0\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"localDev mode uses go run\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // InstallHooks(true, false)\\n    // settings.json contains \\\"go run\\\" and \\\"${FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR}\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"production mode uses entire binary\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // InstallHooks(false, false)\\n    // settings.json contains \\\"entire hooks factoryai-droid\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"force flag reinstalls hooks\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // First install, then InstallHooks(false, true) returns count=7\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"adds permissions.deny rule\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    // InstallHooks(false, false)\\n    // settings.json has \\\"Read(./.entire/metadata/**)\\\" in permissions.deny\\n})\\n```\\n\\n**`TestFactoryAIDroidHelperMethods`** (parallel):\\n\\n```go\\nt.Run(\\\"FormatResumeCommand returns droid --session-id\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    // ag.FormatResumeCommand(\\\"abc123\\\") == \\\"droid --session-id abc123\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"GetHookConfigPath returns .factory/settings.json\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    // ag.GetHookConfigPath() == \\\".factory/settings.json\\\"\\n})\\n```\\n\\n**`TestFactoryAIDroidSessionStubs`** (parallel):\\n\\n```go\\nt.Run(\\\"ReadSession returns not-implemented error\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    // ag.ReadSession(&agent.HookInput{SessionID: \\\"test\\\"}) returns error containing \\\"not implemented\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"WriteSession returns not-implemented error\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    // ag.WriteSession(&agent.AgentSession{}) returns error containing \\\"not implemented\\\"\\n})\\n\\nt.Run(\\\"GetSessionDir returns not-implemented error\\\", func(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    // ag.GetSessionDir(\\\"/some/repo\\\") returns error containing \\\"not implemented\\\"\\n})\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 3. Create `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/setup_factoryai_hooks_test.go`\\n\\nNew file mirroring `setup_gemini_hooks_test.go`.\\n\\nBuild tag: `//go:build integration`\\n\\nPackage: `integration`\\n\\nImports: `\\\"encoding/json\\\"`, `\\\"os\\\"`, `\\\"path/filepath\\\"`, `\\\"testing\\\"`, `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"`\\n\\nType alias: `type FactorySettings = factoryaidroid.FactorySettings`\\n\\n**`TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_AddsAllRequiredHooks`** (parallel):\\n- Create env, InitRepo, InitEntire(\\\"manual-commit\\\")\\n- Create initial commit\\n- `env.RunCLIWithError(\\\"enable\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"factoryai-droid\\\")`\\n- Read `.factory/settings.json` into `FactorySettings`\\n- Verify all 7 hook types present: `SessionStart`, `SessionEnd`, `Stop`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `PreToolUse` (with matcher \\\"Task\\\"), `PostToolUse` (with matcher \\\"Task\\\"), `PreCompact`\\n- Verify `permissions.deny` contains `\\\"Read(./.entire/metadata/**)\\\"` \\n\\n**`TestSetupFactoryAIHooks_PreservesExistingSettings`** (parallel):\\n- Create env, InitRepo, InitEntire\\n- Pre-populate `.factory/settings.json` with custom fields and user hooks:\\n  ```json\\n  {\\n    \\\"customSetting\\\": \\\"should-be-preserved\\\",\\n    \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n      \\\"Stop\\\": [{\\n        \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"echo user-stop-hook\\\"}]\\n      }]\\n    }\\n  }\\n  ```\\n- Run `enable --agent factoryai-droid`\\n- Verify `customSetting` preserved in raw JSON\\n- Verify user's Stop hook preserved (command \\\"echo user-stop-hook\\\" still present)\\n- Verify our hooks added (e.g., `SessionStart`, `PreToolUse`)\\n\\n**Helper function** `readFactorySettingsFile(t *testing.T, env *TestEnv) FactorySettings` -- reads and parses `.factory/settings.json`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 4. Modify `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/agent_strategy_test.go`\\n\\nAdd a new test function `TestFactoryAIDroidAgentStrategyComposition` that verifies the Factory AI Droid hooks create checkpoints through the lifecycle dispatcher.\\n\\n**Key difference from the Claude Code version**: Cannot use `ag.ReadSession()` since it is a stub. Instead, rely entirely on the hook flow. The transcript must be in Droid envelope format so the `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods (`ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`, `ExtractPrompts`) can parse it correctly.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestFactoryAIDroidAgentStrategyComposition(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    \\n    RunForAllStrategies(t, func(t *testing.T, env *TestEnv, strategyName string) {\\n        // Initialize Entire with factoryai-droid agent\\n        // Note: RunForAllStrategies calls NewFeatureBranchEnv which already calls InitEntire\\n        // We need to override with agent-specific init\\n        // OR: Use a custom setup that calls InitEntireWithAgent\\n    })\\n}\\n```\\n\\nWait -- `RunForAllStrategies` calls `NewFeatureBranchEnv` which calls `InitEntire(strategy)` without specifying an agent (defaults to claude-code). For Factory AI Droid tests, we need `InitEntireWithAgent(strategyName, \\\"factoryai-droid\\\")`. This means we cannot use `RunForAllStrategies` directly.\\n\\n**Solution**: Manually iterate strategies and create the env with `InitEntireWithAgent`:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestFactoryAIDroidAgentStrategyComposition(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n    \\n    for _, strat := range AllStrategies() {\\n        strat := strat\\n        t.Run(strat, func(t *testing.T) {\\n            t.Parallel()\\n            \\n            // Create env with Factory AI Droid agent\\n            env := NewRepoWithCommit(t, strat)\\n            // Override agent in settings\\n            env.InitEntireWithAgent(strat, \\\"factoryai-droid\\\")\\n            env.GitCheckoutNewBranch(\\\"feature/factory-test\\\")\\n            \\n            // Create test file\\n            env.WriteFile(\\\"feature.go\\\", \\\"package main\\\\n// new feature\\\")\\n            \\n            // Create Droid session and transcript\\n            session := env.NewFactoryDroidSession()\\n            transcriptPath := session.CreateDroidTranscript(\\\"Add a feature\\\", []FileChange{\\n                {Path: \\\"feature.go\\\", Content: \\\"package main\\\\n// new feature\\\"},\\n            })\\n            \\n            // Simulate hook flow: UserPromptSubmit -> Stop\\n            if err := env.SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmit(session.ID); err != nil {\\n                t.Fatalf(\\\"SimulateFactoryDroidUserPromptSubmit error = %v\\\", err)\\n            }\\n            \\n            if err := env.SimulateFactoryDroidStop(session.ID, transcriptPath); err != nil {\\n                t.Fatalf(\\\"SimulateFactoryDroidStop error = %v\\\", err)\\n            }\\n            \\n            // Verify checkpoint was created\\n            points := env.GetRewindPoints()\\n            if len(points) == 0 {\\n                t.Fatal(\\\"expected at least 1 rewind point after Stop hook\\\")\\n            }\\n        })\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nActually, looking at the code more carefully, `InitEntireWithAgent` won't work here because `NewRepoWithCommit` already calls `InitEntire` via `NewRepoEnv`. We need a different approach. The cleanest way is to use `NewTestEnv`, `InitRepo`, `InitEntireWithAgent`, then manually set up the initial commit and feature branch:\\n\\n```go\\nenv := NewTestEnv(t)\\nenv.InitRepo()\\nenv.InitEntireWithAgent(strat, \\\"factoryai-droid\\\")\\nenv.WriteFile(\\\".gitignore\\\", \\\".entire/\\\\n\\\")\\nenv.WriteFile(\\\"README.md\\\", \\\"# Test Repository\\\")\\nenv.GitAdd(\\\".gitignore\\\")\\nenv.GitAdd(\\\"README.md\\\")\\nenv.GitCommit(\\\"Initial commit\\\")\\nenv.GitCheckoutNewBranch(\\\"feature/factory-test\\\")\\n```\\n\\nThis is the correct approach. It mirrors what `NewFeatureBranchEnv` does but allows specifying the agent.\\n\\n**Also add**: `TestFactoryAIDroidSessionIDTransformation` -- mirrors `TestAgentSessionIDTransformation` but for the Droid agent.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Droid Transcript Builder Details\\n\\nThe `CreateDroidTranscript` method on `FactoryDroidSession` must produce the Droid envelope format. Each JSONL line follows this pattern:\\n\\n**User message:**\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"m1\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Fix the bug\\\"}]}}\\n```\\n\\n**Assistant text message:**\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"m2\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"I'll fix it\\\"}]}}\\n```\\n\\n**Assistant tool use:**\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"m3\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_use\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"toolu_1\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Write\\\",\\\"input\\\":{\\\"file_path\\\":\\\"main.go\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"...\\\"}}]}}\\n```\\n\\n**Tool result (user):**\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"m4\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_result\\\",\\\"tool_use_id\\\":\\\"toolu_1\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Success\\\"}]}}\\n```\\n\\nThis is critical because the `ParseDroidTranscript` function specifically looks for `type:\\\"message\\\"` at the outer level and extracts `role` from the inner message. If we use Claude Code format, the transcript analyzer will not parse any lines.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Potential Challenges\\n\\n1. **TestEnv does not have a `FactoryProjectDir` field.** Unlike `ClaudeProjectDir` and `GeminiProjectDir`, Factory AI Droid does not need one because `GetSessionDir` is a stub. The hook runner can simply omit this from the env vars. No changes to `TestEnv` struct needed.\\n\\n2. **The `initEntireInternal` method re-creates `.entire/settings.json`.** If we call `InitEntireWithAgent` after `NewRepoWithCommit` (which already called `InitEntire`), it will overwrite the settings file. This is actually fine because the settings file is small and idempotent. Alternatively, we can use `NewTestEnv` + manual setup to avoid double initialization.\\n\\n3. **The `enable` command for factoryai-droid.** The `setup_factoryai_hooks_test.go` tests use `Run